          "datePublished": "2023-05-14",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I'm a alumni of this school and i was the first batch of their 11th and 12th standard.  I still remember the school's lack of experience and infrastructure while handling us. We were treated like LAB RATS. They experimented everything using us(first batch). Especially the math teacher, I don't wanna mention his name but i think everyone knows him well for his stereotypical behaviour and awkward speaking skills. He doesn't know the fundamental of mathematics instead he asked us to \"by heart\" the formulas. How will a student understand or development intrest in solving math problems if the teacher asks you to \"by heart\" the formulas rather than to teach them how it's derived? One of my friend attended byjus class from whom I learnt what's sin,cos,tan and their applications and why they're used when I came to know that my mathamatical teacher is not an actual teacher. I lost interest in math and i lost hope in my 11th and 12th. I'm regretting joining this school till date. Please don't join this school or let your child join this school and spoil their higher education. There are hundreds of better schools in Chennai which are more experienced in teaching. If you're joining here, join at your own risk⚠️.\nOne of my senior(Sunil) who studied till 10th from this school sells Pani puri at the entrance gate of the school every evening, please approach him if you have any further questions.",
